  "texts": [
    "As shown, the contact angle stabilizes after approximately 2-3 ns in all cases, confirming that equilibrium wetting is reached within the simulation time.",
    "This behavior is also illustrated in the representative droplet snapshots provided in Figure S1 (for the 50% hydroxylated surface).",
    "The lower part of Figure 7b displays the equilibrium contact angle as a function of the degree of surface functionalization.",
    "Blue squares represent contact angles measured directly from the droplet shape, while black circles correspond to values obtained via the Young-Dupré equation 107, 108, using the calculated work of adhesion:",
    "Here 𝛾 𝑙 was taken as 63.6 mN/m as was previously reported for the SPC/E water 109."
  ],
